Kenneth Morgan Stancil III is accused of fatally shooting his former work-study supervisor Ron Lane at Wayne Community College in North Carolina on Monday . 
  He said he walked 30 miles to Florida after his motorbike broke down and a woman gave him a ride . 
  The woman picked up the 20-year-old who was armed with a knife and covered in tattoos . 
  He is awaiting extradition back to North Carolina . 
  On Tuesday he admitted to killing Lane and said he did it because his former supervisor had molested a relative . 
  His mother said he is 'rattled and confused and needs mental help' She said Lane had made sexually laced comments to her son . 
 